title Settings Registration and Retrieval

|GUI Bootstrap\n(initgui.js)|
start
:Instantiate **SettingsService**;
:Call register('settings', new SettingsService());

|SettingsService|
:Service.init() invoked;
:Delegate to **_init()**;
:Define built-in tab array\n[UsageTab, AccountTab, SecurityTab,\nPersonalizationTab, LanguageTag,\nKeyboardShortcutsTab, AboutTab];

|SettingsService|
partition "**register_tab() Loop** — for each built-in tab" {
    :Call **register_tab(tab)**;
    if (tab instanceof UIElement?) then (yes)
        :Save reference as **ui_element**;
        :Call ui_element.as(**TSettingsTab**)\n→ obtain trait adapter;
        :Call adapter.**get_metadata()**\n→ retrieve metadata object;
        :Build descriptor wrapper:\n{ ...metadata,\n  reinitialize() { ui_element.reinitialize() },\n  get dom() { return ui_element.root } };
        :Assign wrapper as **tab**;
    else (no)
        :Use **tab** as-is\n(plain tab class / object);
    endif
    :Push **tab** into **#tabs** (private array);
}

note right
  All 7 built-in tabs are now
  registered in **#tabs**
end note

|External Caller\n(optional)|
note left
  Any external caller may invoke
  **register_tab(tab)** at any time
  to extend the settings UI
end note
:Call **SettingsService.register_tab(tab)**;

|SettingsService|
:Execute same register_tab() normalisation logic;
:Push additional tab into **#tabs**;

|UIWindowSettings|
:Settings window opens;
:Call globalThis.services.**get('settings')**\n→ obtain SettingsService instance;
:Call svc_settings.**get_tabs()**;

|SettingsService|
:Return **this.#tabs**\n(full array of tab descriptors);

|UIWindowSettings|
:Iterate returned **tabs array**;
:Render tab placeholders and\nbuild Settings UI;
stop

@enduml
